Regression tests for SPARTA rigid-body surface objects (fix rigid)
-------------------------------------------------------------------

run_tests.py runs a set of small input decks and checks the results
against analytic expectations with tolerances:

ballistic     free body with initial velocity + angular momentum:
              straight-line COM motion, constant angular velocity
bounce        body vs static wall via push-off springs: elastic
              rebound within 1%, no tunneling into the cutoff zone
momentum      gas + body momentum conservation in a periodic box,
              within 1.5% statistical drift
overrun       body sweeping 40% of a cell per step through resting
              gas: no particles overrun (deletion counter constant)
remap         overlay / cutcell / incremental remap modes produce
              identical deterministic trajectories
twobody       two bodies colliding head-on via push-off: symmetric,
              elastic within 2%
badmoi        negative: 3d moi violating the triangle inequality
              must be rejected
notwatertight negative: open body group must be rejected

The ballistic, bounce, remap, and twobody tests contain no particles
and must produce identical results on any number of procs.  The
momentum and overrun tests are statistical and use loose tolerances.

Usage:

  python3 run_tests.py --exe ../../../src/spa_serial
  python3 run_tests.py --exe ../../../src/spa_mpi --mpi "mpirun -np 4"

Exit code = number of failed tests.
